value.title: White House facing optics issue with Kamala Harris’ ambitious niece
value.excerpt: Meena Harris, the industrious and outspoken niece of Vice President Kamala Harris, is creating an optics issue for the White House.

value.title: Rep. Jim Banks, chair of largest House conservative caucus, previews GOP agenda post Trump
value.excerpt: In a post-President Trump-era, Rep. Jim Banks is trying to rally the GOP around a new agenda that embraces popular Trump stances with a return to conservative fiscal responsibility.

value.title: Former Trump DHS officials Wolf, Cuccinelli, Morgan join Heritage Foundation
value.excerpt: Three former Trump-era Homeland Security officials, including former acting Secretary Chad Wolf, have joined the Heritage Foundation as fellows -- the latest move to a think tank by ex-Trump officials since leaving office.

value.title: Analysis: Covering Obama, then Trump, now Biden: What's changed?
value.excerpt: We're now more than a week out of the Trump era and a week into the Biden era.

value.title: Donald Trump Expects Impeachment Trial to Be 'Badge of Honor'—But Rethinks 2024 Run
value.excerpt: The ex-president wanted to use the trial to relitigate his claims of election fraud, but Lindsey Graham told him, "You don't want to go there."

value.title: Kamala Harris’ Stepdaughter Ella Emhoff’s Modeling Contract Sparks Melania Trump Comparisons On Twitter
value.excerpt: Some Twitter users were not impressed with Kamala Harris' stepdaughter Ella Emhoff signing a modeling contract, while others compared the 22-year-old's situation with that of former first lady Melania Trump,

value.title: Kamala Harris TV appearance in West Virginia surprises Manchin: 'That's not working together'
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris promoted the Biden administration’s "critical" coronavirus "American Rescue Plan" this week in a pair of interviews with local TV stations in West Virginia and Arizona.

value.title: Tucker: Dems' rhetoric, actions show they're 'more afraid now that Donald Trump has left office'
value.excerpt: Democrats and their allies in Big Tech and the media are doing more than just attacking their political opponents, host Tucker Carlson argued Friday on "Tucker Carlson Tonight."

value.title: Something AOC, Trump Jr. and Ted Cruz can all agree on: GameStop
value.excerpt: Stocks in the video game retailer and other struggling companies saw huge rallies that blindsided some of the most powerful players on Wall Street.

value.title: Nancy Sinatra will 'never forgive' Trump supporters 'ever,' singer says
value.excerpt: "Somethin' Stupid" singer and daughter of Frank Sinatra, Nancy Sinatra, said she'll "never forgive" supporters of former President Donald Trump.

value.title: Politico reporter: Trump base is 'getting stronger' since he left office, impeachment would only empower him
value.excerpt: Politico reporter Tara Palmeri suggested on Friday that President Trump may have more political clout among his supporters than the D.C. establishment and the mainstream media assumed he had since he left office.

value.title: Federal appeals court allows US border officials to swiftly return unaccompanied migrant children under Trump-era policy
value.excerpt: A federal appeals court ruled Friday that the federal government can quickly return unaccompanied migrant children apprehended at the US-Mexico border under a public health order put in place under former President Donald Trump.

value.title: Biden visits wounded soldiers at Walter Reed, where son died
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden has made his first major foray outside the White House with a visit to Walter Reed National Military Medical Center to meet with wounded soldiers

value.title: Facebook's Sandberg praises Biden abortion policy, criticizes South Carolina partial ban
value.excerpt: Facebook Chief Operating Officer Sheryl Sandberg is praising President Bident's recent executive order on overseas abortion providers and criticizing South Carolina's legislation banning most abortions.

value.title: Biden renews deportation relief for Syrians in the United States
value.excerpt: The administration of President Joe Biden on Friday extended deportation relief for several thousand Syrian immigrants living in the United States, an early move that aligns with his broader pro-immigrant platform.

value.title: AOC, Green New Dealers rejoice over Biden’s climate plan: ‘It’s almost as if we helped shape the platform’
value.excerpt: Advocates for the Green New Deal have praised the Biden administration for its early moves to address climate change, taking a victory lap after the president signed a slew of sweeping executive orders targeting the environment.

value.title: Biden pledge to reopen PLO mission in Washington faces legal hurdles
value.excerpt: U.S. President Joe Biden's plan to work to reopen the Palestinians' diplomatic mission in Washington could be held up over a law that exposes Palestinian officials to U.S. anti-terror lawsuits, officials and advisers to the Palestinians say.

value.title: Cuomo blames nursing home scandal on 'political attack' by Trump admin
value.excerpt: In his first public comments since a scathing attorney general report finding New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo’s administration undercounted nursing home deaths, the governor on Friday argued criticisms of him were a "political attack" that began with the Trump administration.

value.title: Hawley rips Biden's 40 executive orders, 'radical policies': 'An attempt to govern by executive fiat'
value.excerpt: President Biden's 40 executive orders show that he is pursuing a "far-left agenda" that will kill American energy jobs, Sen. Josh Hawley, R-Mo., said on Friday.

value.title: Biden taps Iran envoy to face challenges of confronting both Tehran and polarized views at home
value.excerpt: The Biden administration has tapped Robert Malley, a progressive foreign policy expert who served on the Obama administration's negotiating team for the Iran nuclear deal, as its new top envoy for Iran.

value.title: New Georgia runoffs data finds that more Black voters than usual came out. Trump voters stayed home.
value.excerpt: Our analysis finds two notable patterns that could account for the wins: high turnout among Black voters and low turnout in the predominantly White and rural precincts that had supported incumbent President Donald Trump — where voters were more likely to believe Trump’s baseless allegations of electoral fraud.

value.title: The fired Fox News editor behind the network's Arizona election call for Biden says he became the target of 'murderous rage' from viewers
value.excerpt: Chris Stirewalt, who oversaw the Fox News Decision Desk during 2020 election coverage, was fired last week after being exiled from air.

value.title: DeSantis: Florida deserves federal help — Governor proposes $1B climate initiative — Morgan & Biden? — Gaetz bashes Cheney in Wyoming
value.excerpt: When Gov. Ron DeSantis laid out his $96 billion budget plan on Thursday, he was unapologetic that the billions of dollars that came out of Washington, D.C., have helped the state deal with the fallout from an economic collapse.

value.title: ‘The perfect target’: Russia cultivated Trump as asset for 40 years – ex-KGB spy
value.excerpt: The KGB ‘played the game as if they were immensely impressed by his personality’, Yuri Shvets, a key source for a new book, tells the Guardian

value.title: ‘Trump Just Used Us and Our Fear’: One Woman’s Journey Out of QAnon
value.excerpt: During the political fallout after four years of Donald J. Trump, one question is what will happen with the followers of conspiracy theories that bend Americans’ perceptions of reality.
